1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,321 --> 00:01:37,893
=Episode 9=
(For Us, She Married Again)

3
00:02:04,221 --> 00:02:05,020
What do you want?

4
00:02:06,701 --> 00:02:09,221
I need to find
my middle school graduation photo.

5
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:18,461
Found it?

6
00:02:20,781 --> 00:02:21,901
Still looking.

7
00:02:23,820 --> 00:02:24,860
I'll help you look for it.

8
00:02:25,301 --> 00:02:26,181
We'll find it.

9
00:02:29,741 --> 00:02:31,700
People called me crazy.
So you got into a fight?

10
00:02:32,941 --> 00:02:34,021
They can't insult you.

11
00:02:36,700 --> 00:02:38,301
Don't go out alone anymore.

12
00:02:39,461 --> 00:02:40,860
Don't fight for me.

13
00:02:42,461 --> 00:02:43,980
What can I do for you?

14
00:02:44,781 --> 00:02:46,181
Don't manage it all on your own.

15
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:48,700
What do you mean?

16
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:53,580
Did you post those things on the forum?

17
00:02:54,941 --> 00:02:57,181
And the medical bills from Qingzhou?

18
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:00,660
You have them, right?

19
00:03:05,341 --> 00:03:07,221
I know what you're trying to do.

20
00:03:08,580 --> 00:03:09,380
You don't.

21
00:03:10,980 --> 00:03:12,301
You don't need to know.

22
00:03:13,420 --> 00:03:14,700
I've seen that diary.

23
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:17,341
What diary?

24
00:03:18,181 --> 00:03:19,420
When you returned from the US,

25
00:03:19,420 --> 00:03:20,941
I saw you and Bai Shu

26
00:03:20,941 --> 00:03:22,744
- wrote it together.
- There is no diary.

27
00:03:24,221 --> 00:03:25,140
Stop overthinking.

28
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:29,301
If it's for you and Bai Shu,

29
00:03:29,501 --> 00:03:30,540
I'll do anything.

30
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:31,781
Count me in.

31
00:03:35,869 --> 00:03:36,941
(2004, Qidaohezi)

32
00:03:36,941 --> 00:03:38,424
It's your turn to keep it.

33
00:03:38,621 --> 00:03:39,301
I don't want it.

34
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:43,741
We agreed.

35
00:03:45,501 --> 00:03:46,741
I missed one exam.

36
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:48,820
I won't get into Yucai.

37
00:03:50,140 --> 00:03:51,621
We won't see each other again.

38
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:53,621
Keep the pen.

39
00:03:58,980 --> 00:04:00,140
It was an accident.

40
00:04:00,781 --> 00:04:02,040
Not everything is an accident.

41
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:06,260
Was it an accident
I was born into that family?

42
00:04:10,301 --> 00:04:12,181
Was it an accident
that I have such a brother?

43
00:04:15,461 --> 00:04:17,181
There are no accidents in this world.

44
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:19,941
You've had it too easy.

45
00:04:19,941 --> 00:04:21,260
You don't understand anything.

46
00:04:52,216 --> 00:04:53,460
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
So good.

47
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:56,181
(Friendship Eatery)
Your hometown has so much food.

48
00:04:57,661 --> 00:04:58,741
What's my treat?

49
00:04:58,981 --> 00:04:59,780
Almost there.

50
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:02,700
You know what?
This place's Guo Bao Rou is amazing.

51
00:05:03,101 --> 00:05:04,460
I came here a lot as a kid.

52
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:05,944
(Friendship Eatery)
Then I must try it.

53
00:05:07,501 --> 00:05:09,140
Sir? Sir?

54
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:10,101
Coming!

55
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:10,900
Guo Bao Rou, split.

56
00:05:10,900 --> 00:05:11,741
And two sodas.

57
00:05:11,941 --> 00:05:12,501
Got it.

58
00:05:12,621 --> 00:05:13,260
Hurry up.

59
00:05:13,340 --> 00:05:14,741
Okay. Please have a seat.

60
00:05:18,020 --> 00:05:19,820
(Friendship Forever)
Liu Xiaoran is so cunning.

61
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:23,580
At this critical moment,
he went all out online.

62
00:05:23,580 --> 00:05:24,621
With those shady moves,

63
00:05:24,621 --> 00:05:26,460
now everyone knows
your brother hit someone,

64
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:29,020
and everyone thinks your
whole family is crazy.

65
00:05:29,621 --> 00:05:30,700
He's so sneaky.

66
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:33,580
If you ever do anything
against him from now on,

67
00:05:34,101 --> 00:05:35,741
people will think you're not only crazy,

68
00:05:35,861 --> 00:05:39,101
but also an ungrateful crazy person.

69
00:05:39,421 --> 00:05:40,900
Truly underhanded.

70
00:05:41,941 --> 00:05:43,340
What a bad guy, huh?

71
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:45,580
How are you planning to fight back?

72
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:47,421
Divorce.

73
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:51,541
Seriously? For real?

74
00:05:51,621 --> 00:05:52,421
Yeah.

75
00:05:53,181 --> 00:05:54,580
Not only will I divorce him.

76
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:55,981
I'll do it publicly.

77
00:05:56,501 --> 00:05:57,941
Guo Bao Rou is ready.

78
00:05:59,501 --> 00:06:00,181
Thanks, sir.

79
00:06:00,181 --> 00:06:00,820
Here you go.

80
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:02,220
Alright, divorce him.

81
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:04,900
Eat well, divorce well.

82
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:06,621
As in pear soda.

83
00:06:09,340 --> 00:06:10,380
Here, try it.

84
00:06:13,336 --> 00:06:15,181
(Breathe by Liu Xiaoran)
Recently, renowned author Liu Xiaoran

85
00:06:15,181 --> 00:06:17,621
sued his longtime publisher in court.

86
00:06:17,981 --> 00:06:19,741
It's reported the dispute arose

87
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,260
because the publisher
printed extra copies

88
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:23,741
without his consent.

89
00:06:25,101 --> 00:06:27,192
The book of Breathe has been pulled
from all shelves.

90
00:06:28,301 --> 00:06:29,700
Liu Xiaoran responded

91
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:32,780
that until the overprinting dispute
is properly resolved,

92
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:35,340
"Breathe" will not
be available for sale.

93
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:36,189
(Liang Yi)

94
00:06:37,340 --> 00:06:38,020
What's up?

95
00:06:38,301 --> 00:06:40,181
Liu Xiaoran is really something.

96
00:06:40,301 --> 00:06:42,101
He just trashed you online as crazy.

97
00:06:42,301 --> 00:06:44,780
Then he found an excuse
to pull the books entirely.

98
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:47,020
A diversion tactic.

99
00:06:47,181 --> 00:06:49,580
He's deliberately distracting the public

100
00:06:50,181 --> 00:06:53,460
to minimize the impact
the copyright case might have.

101
00:06:53,941 --> 00:06:55,380
The publisher didn't refute it.

102
00:06:55,580 --> 00:06:56,900
They must be in cahoots.

103
00:06:57,301 --> 00:06:59,220
I knew the vested interests
behind Liu Xiaoran

104
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:01,260
would spare no expense
to protect this cash cow.

105
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:02,421
Forget about them.

106
00:07:02,580 --> 00:07:04,181
We'll fight this lawsuit by any means.

107
00:07:04,981 --> 00:07:07,380
I'm worried
this is Liu Xiaoran's elaborate scheme.

108
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:09,421
Our copyright evidence
was weak from the start.

109
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:10,541
And now,

110
00:07:10,661 --> 00:07:11,861
if he suddenly claims

111
00:07:12,061 --> 00:07:14,780
that you're pursuing
this copyright case for personal gain

112
00:07:14,941 --> 00:07:16,981
and conspiring
with the publisher to frame him,

113
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:19,780
not only will we
lose the copyright case,

114
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:22,140
but you'll also be branded
as an outsider's ally

115
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:24,140
for framing your own husband.

116
00:07:25,541 --> 00:07:26,661
If he really says that,

117
00:07:26,661 --> 00:07:27,861
what can I do?

118
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:29,780
I can't stoop to his level

119
00:07:29,861 --> 00:07:31,301
and use those lowly tactics, right?

120
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:33,820
Just think carefully about what I said.

121
00:07:34,301 --> 00:07:35,140
Alright.

122
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:38,780
He's back. I need to go.

123
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:53,580
The oranges are nice.

124
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:58,941
With the new book pulled,
you still have the mood for oranges?

125
00:08:03,220 --> 00:08:05,621
With the extra copies,
the publisher is robbing us blind.

126
00:08:06,421 --> 00:08:09,340
I'm suing them
purely to protect our interests.

127
00:08:09,741 --> 00:08:11,101
And that thing with Xiaofei,

128
00:08:12,101 --> 00:08:14,820
we spent a solid 200,000 yuan on that.

129
00:08:15,941 --> 00:08:17,861
But it matters not.
He's my brother-in-law.

130
00:08:19,861 --> 00:08:22,741
I handled this PR crisis
very quickly and efficiently.

131
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:23,941
Aren't you rewarding me?

132
00:08:24,340 --> 00:08:25,020
For what?

133
00:08:26,181 --> 00:08:28,421
For successfully branding me
as a lunatic?

134
00:08:30,541 --> 00:08:32,980
I need to explain this matter
to you properly.

135
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,340
Online leaks say you're mentally ill.

136
00:08:35,340 --> 00:08:36,781
I didn't say that.

137
00:08:37,181 --> 00:08:40,620
I've been giving my all
to handle Xiaofei's troubles.

138
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,301
Did you offend someone?

139
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:44,980
Those proofs are real.

140
00:08:45,661 --> 00:08:49,141
Should I have the company's PR
and legal team handle it for you?

141
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:50,740
Not necessary.

142
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,661
Let me remind you,

143
00:08:53,980 --> 00:08:55,381
Xiaofei isn't my problem.

144
00:08:56,261 --> 00:08:57,141
You are.

145
00:08:58,421 --> 00:08:58,941
I won't eat.

146
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:00,340
Just one orange.

147
00:09:00,781 --> 00:09:01,541
Why so stingy?

148
00:09:02,141 --> 00:09:04,141
From now on,
we'll account for every penny.

149
00:09:06,021 --> 00:09:06,860
Check your phone.

150
00:09:14,397 --> 00:09:17,301
(Property Division Agreement)

151
00:09:17,301 --> 00:09:18,100
Read it carefully.

152
00:09:18,941 --> 00:09:20,301
If you object, get a lawyer.

153
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:22,340
I'm stingy. I won't compromise.

154
00:09:30,941 --> 00:09:31,740
Divorce?

155
00:09:33,141 --> 00:09:34,141
Are you serious?

156
00:09:35,181 --> 00:09:35,941
Is it necessary?

157
00:09:37,421 --> 00:09:38,328
It is.

158
00:09:41,421 --> 00:09:43,860
It's because I now have a strategy
in the copyright lawsuit,

159
00:09:43,980 --> 00:09:45,500
and you're not winning now, right?

160
00:09:45,901 --> 00:09:47,781
You could've come to me
for a settlement.

161
00:09:47,941 --> 00:09:49,500
Use divorce as a threat?

162
00:09:49,781 --> 00:09:51,781
You think I'm bluffing
about divorcing you?

163
00:09:52,460 --> 00:09:53,740
Besides the copyright lawsuit,

164
00:09:53,820 --> 00:09:56,100
I can't think of any reason
for us to divorce.

165
00:09:56,261 --> 00:09:57,661
First, I made it clear to you.

166
00:09:58,541 --> 00:10:00,620
For the copyright case,
a settlement is impossible.

167
00:10:00,941 --> 00:10:02,168
We're going to court.

168
00:10:02,421 --> 00:10:05,740
Also, shouldn't the divorce
be related to marital breakdown?

169
00:10:06,021 --> 00:10:08,541
How is it related
to the copyright lawsuit?

170
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,141
There's nothing wrong with our marriage.

171
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:15,021
The problem
is that you think nothing is wrong.

172
00:10:17,181 --> 00:10:18,301
Plagiarism is fine with you.

173
00:10:19,381 --> 00:10:21,141
You discovered
I sent money to another man,

174
00:10:21,141 --> 00:10:22,460
and you still think it's fine.

175
00:10:22,941 --> 00:10:24,340
That's your problem. Understand?

176
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:26,100
I knew it.

177
00:10:26,781 --> 00:10:28,340
I'm the one sparing no effort

178
00:10:28,340 --> 00:10:29,980
to protect our shared interests.

179
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:31,100
And you?

180
00:10:31,661 --> 00:10:33,460
You want the copyright and a divorce.

181
00:10:33,661 --> 00:10:35,460
You just want
to destroy our current life.

182
00:10:36,661 --> 00:10:38,141
I don't understand.

183
00:10:39,661 --> 00:10:40,820
I won't agree to divorce.

184
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,421
Our divorce isn't up to you.

185
00:10:45,141 --> 00:10:45,901
See you in court.

186
00:10:52,141 --> 00:10:54,220
Are you playing some tricks?

187
00:10:55,941 --> 00:10:56,620
What tricks?

188
00:11:03,181 --> 00:11:04,740
You see the pie I've grown now,

189
00:11:04,980 --> 00:11:06,301
and you want a bigger slice?

190
00:11:07,661 --> 00:11:08,580
Let me remind you,

191
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:11,941
the Marriage Law
protects the innocent party.

192
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,261
The guilty party pays the price.

193
00:11:15,181 --> 00:11:17,661
You'd better take back
this Property Division Agreement.

194
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:20,620
Don't force us into court.

195
00:11:21,141 --> 00:11:22,941
Otherwise, you'll be the one
to be humiliated

196
00:11:23,460 --> 00:11:24,781
and lose everything.

197
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:27,460
Don't play your tricks too hard.

198
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:28,740
If too hard,

199
00:11:29,181 --> 00:11:31,661
that would be ruthless self-destruction.

200
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:33,181
Thank you.

201
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:35,100
Thank you for telling me all this.

202
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:38,141
It makes me feel divorcing you
is the most correct choice I've made.

203
00:11:40,181 --> 00:11:40,980
That's right.

204
00:11:41,661 --> 00:11:42,860
Divorce runs in your family.

205
00:11:43,220 --> 00:11:44,661
Your mom's been married four times.

206
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:46,541
You'll definitely outdo her.

207
00:12:01,620 --> 00:12:02,901
You're both the same.

208
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:07,500
Anyone who gets stuck
with you is unlucky.

209
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:26,718
(Qidaohezi, 2004)

210
00:12:35,181 --> 00:12:37,980
Ren Xiaoming, take food to your brother.

211
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:42,100
I can't go. My hand hurts.

212
00:12:45,141 --> 00:12:46,740
Who are you putting on this act for?

213
00:12:47,301 --> 00:12:48,381
No one owes you anything.

214
00:12:49,661 --> 00:12:51,381
Did your brother get sick on purpose?

215
00:12:52,301 --> 00:12:54,181
Did we make you
fail your exams on purpose?

216
00:12:55,301 --> 00:12:57,941
When something happens to the family,
we all bear it together.

217
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,661
I'm not putting on an act.

218
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:03,901
So what if I fail the exam?

219
00:13:04,141 --> 00:13:06,381
My hand hurts. I can't go.

220
00:13:06,781 --> 00:13:08,301
Can't the family show some tolerance?

221
00:13:19,460 --> 00:13:20,580
I will hold it up for you.

222
00:13:26,381 --> 00:13:27,421
Let me tell you something.

223
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,740
In a few days, Mr. Sun is coming
to our place for dinner.

224
00:13:31,941 --> 00:13:32,980
The thing between us...

225
00:13:38,261 --> 00:13:39,620
It is pretty much settled.

226
00:13:43,381 --> 00:13:44,632
The household registration...

227
00:13:52,661 --> 00:13:53,500
You carry it daily.

228
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:54,700
Wherever you go, it goes.

229
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:56,781
You'll just give it to me?

230
00:14:02,301 --> 00:14:04,980
Mr. Sun arranged a hospital for Xiaofei.

231
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,661
He also promised
to cover all the medical costs.

232
00:14:09,141 --> 00:14:10,381
Once we're officially married,

233
00:14:11,021 --> 00:14:13,181
our whole family will move to La City.

234
00:14:14,661 --> 00:14:15,901
He has many places.

235
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:17,860
You'll have your own room too.

236
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:20,301
No more sleeping
on the living room couch.

237
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:24,541
Don't you have anything to say?

238
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:26,340
I said it.

239
00:14:26,781 --> 00:14:27,781
What did you say?

240
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:29,740
I said, "Hmm."

241
00:14:38,740 --> 00:14:41,141
("Hmm" is the weakest answer.)

242
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:43,661
(It means not wanting this)

243
00:14:44,261 --> 00:14:45,421
(but being powerless.)

244
00:15:12,381 --> 00:15:13,740
Xiaoming, stop lying around.

245
00:15:15,220 --> 00:15:17,141
Quick, help me move the table over here.

246
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:19,181
Isn't Xiaofei better now?

247
00:15:19,181 --> 00:15:20,220
Why don't you call him?

248
00:15:20,301 --> 00:15:21,141
Xiaofei!

249
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,220
Food is ready, Xiaofei.

250
00:15:25,661 --> 00:15:26,661
Get up now.

251
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:31,301
Come on.

252
00:15:32,781 --> 00:15:34,301
Mom, I'll get the tableware for you.

253
00:15:36,181 --> 00:15:37,432
Where do I put it?

254
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:39,220
This is the seat of honor.

255
00:15:39,220 --> 00:15:40,860
Mr. Sun will sit here later.

256
00:15:41,021 --> 00:15:41,941
Put the stool there.

257
00:15:42,181 --> 00:15:43,740
Later, you'll sit in your usual spot.

258
00:15:46,460 --> 00:15:47,620
Slow down. Careful.

259
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:49,620
Alright.

260
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:52,781
Good.

261
00:15:53,901 --> 00:15:55,181
You'll sit here later.

262
00:16:00,980 --> 00:16:01,580
Don't sit now.

263
00:16:01,620 --> 00:16:02,740
Get up first. Get up.

264
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:04,280
The guest isn't here.

265
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:05,541
The guest of honor isn't here.

266
00:16:05,541 --> 00:16:06,421
You sat down first?

267
00:16:06,421 --> 00:16:07,421
Stand over there first.

268
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,500
Wait.

269
00:16:13,620 --> 00:16:14,700
Be polite.

270
00:16:15,941 --> 00:16:16,781
Listen to me.

271
00:16:20,381 --> 00:16:22,541
Alright. Is it necessary
for such a small thing?

272
00:16:22,901 --> 00:16:23,941
- He's here.
- So nagging.

273
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:25,496
Alright.

274
00:16:25,901 --> 00:16:26,901
Okay.

275
00:16:27,141 --> 00:16:27,941
Take your seat.

276
00:16:27,941 --> 00:16:29,661
- The food's ready?
- The food is just ready.

277
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:30,661
This is your seat.

278
00:16:30,941 --> 00:16:32,141
- Okay.
- Sit here.

279
00:16:33,381 --> 00:16:35,661
This project benefits
the country and the people.

280
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:37,301
The direction is definitely sound.

281
00:16:37,860 --> 00:16:39,220
Why listen to him?

282
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:40,781
He knows nothing.

283
00:16:41,661 --> 00:16:44,381
Trust me, this project will make
at least eight to ten million.

284
00:16:45,541 --> 00:16:48,181
Just like you said, I'll come
to your place for drinks another day.

285
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:49,112
I need to go.

286
00:16:49,620 --> 00:16:51,460
Mr. Sun, hurry, sit.
Take the seat of honor.

287
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:53,464
- Hurry.
- I'm moving my car.

288
00:16:54,941 --> 00:16:55,740
M-Moving?

289
00:17:04,101 --> 00:17:05,020
Big Mercedes.

290
00:17:05,980 --> 00:17:06,901
You little gremlins!

291
00:17:07,141 --> 00:17:08,300
Can't you just wait a minute?

292
00:17:10,101 --> 00:17:11,941
Honestly, you two are driving me crazy.

293
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:14,008
You can't wait.

294
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,980
- Mr. Sun.
- Come on.

295
00:17:16,980 --> 00:17:18,780
Just take the seat of honor.

296
00:17:18,901 --> 00:17:20,661
Parking spots
are hard to find around here.

297
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:22,540
This seat?

298
00:17:22,941 --> 00:17:24,460
Yes. The seat of honor.

299
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:25,821
Come on.

300
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:29,941
Here.

301
00:17:31,621 --> 00:17:32,300
Make a toast.

302
00:17:33,740 --> 00:17:35,780
They're already eating like this.
Why bother?

303
00:17:37,181 --> 00:17:38,020
Make a toast.

304
00:17:38,821 --> 00:17:41,381
After all, this is the first time
we're eating together.

305
00:17:41,661 --> 00:17:44,381
After this meal,
you'll be the head of the household.

306
00:17:44,941 --> 00:17:46,181
All this formality.

307
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:47,101
I'll make a toast.

308
00:17:47,421 --> 00:17:48,440
Stop eating, you two.

309
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:50,740
Go ahead.

310
00:17:52,020 --> 00:17:54,141
Xiaofei has been discharged.

311
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:56,141
Your mom and I are now married.

312
00:17:56,980 --> 00:17:58,500
This counts as two happy events.

313
00:17:58,941 --> 00:17:59,780
That's it then.

314
00:18:00,460 --> 00:18:01,300
I'll make a toast.

315
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:02,980
They are my children.

316
00:18:03,980 --> 00:18:04,901
He is my husband.

317
00:18:06,141 --> 00:18:07,700
It wasn't you who chose each other.

318
00:18:07,861 --> 00:18:09,381
It was me who put you together.

319
00:18:09,780 --> 00:18:10,980
Because I wanted a home.

320
00:18:11,581 --> 00:18:12,700
You wanted a home?

321
00:18:12,941 --> 00:18:14,460
That place that is not too big?

322
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:15,581
Yes.

323
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:17,381
Come on, let's drink the wine.

324
00:18:17,661 --> 00:18:19,621
Drink the water, and we'll be a family.

325
00:18:19,941 --> 00:18:21,941
Eat well today, and live well
from now on. Cheers!

326
00:18:22,421 --> 00:18:22,941
Cheers!

327
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:35,512
Well...

328
00:18:35,700 --> 00:18:36,260
Mr. Sun.

329
00:18:49,101 --> 00:18:50,020
Buddy, make some room.

330
00:18:51,229 --> 00:18:53,060
(Qidaohezi Qidian Middle School
Announcement Board)

331
00:18:53,060 --> 00:18:54,141
Buddy, move aside.

332
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,421
Make way.

333
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:57,540
Make way.

334
00:18:57,540 --> 00:18:58,460
Make way.

335
00:19:01,816 --> 00:19:04,408
(High School Admission List)

336
00:19:05,941 --> 00:19:06,780
Where am I?

337
00:19:10,584 --> 00:19:11,740
Zhang Fang, you're here.

338
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:13,941
I got in! No. 7 High School.

339
00:19:13,941 --> 00:19:15,020
I got into high school!

340
00:19:15,020 --> 00:19:15,540
(Vocational High Schools)

341
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:18,181
Dad promised me a private theater
if I get into high school.

342
00:19:18,181 --> 00:19:19,020
It's a done deal.

343
00:19:20,024 --> 00:19:21,220
You're here.

344
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,101
Where's Xiaoming?

345
00:19:22,101 --> 00:19:23,608
(He Yuqiong, No. 7 High School)
We're classmates again.

346
00:19:23,821 --> 00:19:26,260
Three years together,
and three more to go.

347
00:19:27,341 --> 00:19:28,664
We're comrades-in-arms again.

348
00:19:32,381 --> 00:19:33,060
No way.

349
00:19:38,301 --> 00:19:39,709
(Ren Xiaoming, Yucai High School)

350
00:19:40,581 --> 00:19:42,341
Ren Xiaoming, you got in!

351
00:19:42,540 --> 00:19:43,780
You got into Yucai!

352
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:47,381
I told you that you'd definitely get in.

353
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,060
That's impossible.

354
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:51,540
What's so impossible?

355
00:19:51,540 --> 00:19:53,181
It's written there clearly.

356
00:19:53,821 --> 00:19:55,381
How could I possibly have gotten in?

357
00:19:56,101 --> 00:19:57,941
Dude, you already got in.

358
00:19:57,941 --> 00:19:58,980
What do you mean by that?

359
00:19:58,980 --> 00:19:59,780
Keep it down.

360
00:20:02,181 --> 00:20:03,381
Bai Shu got in too.

361
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:04,861
It'd be weird if she didn't.

362
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:06,341
That's true.

363
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:07,060
Where's she?

364
00:20:08,060 --> 00:20:08,740
Bai Shu?

365
00:20:17,740 --> 00:20:19,101
What's up with you two lately?

366
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:21,540
We're done.

367
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:23,341
Why?

368
00:20:24,141 --> 00:20:25,629
- Ms. Zhou.
- Ms. Zhou.

369
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,020
- Hello, Ms. Zhou.
- Ms. Zhou.

370
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,141
Ren Xiaoming.

371
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:31,640
- Ms. Zhou.
- Ms. Zhou.

372
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:32,460
Congratulations.

373
00:20:33,621 --> 00:20:35,901
Ms. Zhou, I missed one entire subject.

374
00:20:36,341 --> 00:20:37,661
How could I still get into Yucai?

375
00:20:38,341 --> 00:20:40,504
You appear to meet
the district enrollment policy.

376
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:43,381
What's the district enrollment policy?

377
00:20:44,020 --> 00:20:47,341
It means your hukou
is within Yucai's enrollment district.

378
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:49,700
Your score requirement could be lowered.

379
00:20:50,581 --> 00:20:51,861
It still doesn't make sense.

380
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,621
The school is in La City.

381
00:20:53,621 --> 00:20:55,101
My hukou is in Qidaohezi.

382
00:20:56,901 --> 00:20:59,060
I'm not too sure about the specifics.

383
00:20:59,901 --> 00:21:01,821
But regardless, congratulations.

384
00:21:03,141 --> 00:21:04,661
Bai Shu also got into Yucai.

385
00:21:04,901 --> 00:21:06,861
So you two will still be classmates.

386
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:11,101
Here, take this.

387
00:21:13,381 --> 00:21:14,460
She gave it to you?

388
00:21:16,780 --> 00:21:18,360
If she doesn't want it, neither do I.

389
00:21:19,421 --> 00:21:20,952
If she doesn't want it, neither do I.

390
00:21:31,901 --> 00:21:34,101
When Bai Shu returned this pen to me,

391
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:38,141
she said the exact same thing
you just did.

392
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:44,421
Goodbye, Ms. Zhou.

393
00:21:57,341 --> 00:21:59,260
(Bai Shu and I said the same thing.)

394
00:22:00,141 --> 00:22:01,880
(But our motivations were different.)

395
00:22:02,341 --> 00:22:04,581
(One came from malice
after wounded pride.)

396
00:22:05,901 --> 00:22:08,421
(The other was trying
to preserve equality between friends.)

397
00:22:09,740 --> 00:22:11,700
(Why does she always do better than me?)

398
00:22:14,260 --> 00:22:14,780
Hand it over.

399
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:16,901
- Get lost! Get lost!
- It's fine.

400
00:22:16,901 --> 00:22:17,581
- What?
- No.

401
00:22:17,581 --> 00:22:19,540
- Such language at such a young age!
- No.

402
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:21,141
Discipline him now, or he'll be a punk.

403
00:22:21,141 --> 00:22:22,141
You're the punk!

404
00:22:22,141 --> 00:22:22,980
What?

405
00:22:23,381 --> 00:22:24,341
You won't do anything?

406
00:22:24,581 --> 00:22:25,861
- I'll do it for you.
- I will.

407
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:27,821
Just carry him inside.

408
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:28,901
Close the door.

409
00:22:29,272 --> 00:22:29,980
Go back.

410
00:22:29,980 --> 00:22:30,740
- Get lost!
- I will.

411
00:22:30,780 --> 00:22:31,480
Go to your room.

412
00:22:31,661 --> 00:22:33,460
- Let him have some peace.
- Get lost!

413
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:35,128
- Get down. Go back.
- Leave him be.

414
00:22:35,421 --> 00:22:36,141
Get lost!

415
00:22:36,141 --> 00:22:37,181
You want me to get lost?

416
00:22:37,421 --> 00:22:38,181
You go back.

417
00:22:38,220 --> 00:22:39,181
- Listen.
- Let him go!

418
00:22:39,300 --> 00:22:39,980
Let him go!

419
00:22:39,980 --> 00:22:40,500
Get away!

420
00:22:40,621 --> 00:22:42,101
- Get out!
- Stop hitting him!

421
00:22:42,101 --> 00:22:43,020
- Go back!
- Get lost!

422
00:22:43,341 --> 00:22:44,141
Get away!

423
00:22:44,581 --> 00:22:45,141
Get lost!

424
00:22:45,141 --> 00:22:45,780
Go back!

425
00:22:45,780 --> 00:22:46,861
I'll deal with you today!

426
00:22:47,941 --> 00:22:48,901
Let him go!

427
00:22:49,220 --> 00:22:50,341
- What are you doing?
- Let Xiaofei go!

428
00:22:50,341 --> 00:22:51,980
- Stop!
- Let Xiaofei go!

429
00:22:51,980 --> 00:22:52,621
Let him go!

430
00:22:52,621 --> 00:22:53,700
Go! Just go!

431
00:22:53,980 --> 00:22:54,941
Hurry up. Go.

432
00:22:55,101 --> 00:22:55,941
Go. Just go.

433
00:22:56,260 --> 00:22:57,460
Come with me. Calm down.

434
00:22:57,621 --> 00:22:59,020
Hurry up. Just go.

435
00:23:03,540 --> 00:23:04,540
You also want me to go?

436
00:23:07,141 --> 00:23:07,928
Fine.

437
00:23:09,901 --> 00:23:11,101
To take your son to a doctor,

438
00:23:12,780 --> 00:23:14,141
I pulled strings,

439
00:23:14,780 --> 00:23:16,220
smiled, and spent money.

440
00:23:16,661 --> 00:23:17,624
He told me to get lost.

441
00:23:18,381 --> 00:23:19,381
To get her into Yucai,

442
00:23:20,141 --> 00:23:23,821
I gave gifts, greased palms,
transferred hukou, and paid sponsorship.

443
00:23:23,821 --> 00:23:24,740
She tried to stab me.

444
00:23:26,941 --> 00:23:28,181
What haven't I done?

445
00:23:31,341 --> 00:23:32,020
Exhausting.

446
00:23:33,101 --> 00:23:34,101
Really exhausting.

447
00:23:41,181 --> 00:23:41,780
Meiyan,

448
00:23:42,861 --> 00:23:44,220
tell me, what am I doing this for?

449
00:23:55,101 --> 00:23:56,740
So you rushed into marriage

450
00:23:57,980 --> 00:24:00,101
just to transfer my hukou
and get me into Yucai?

451
00:24:03,661 --> 00:24:07,460
I didn't tell you because I was afraid
it would hurt your pride.

452
00:24:15,581 --> 00:24:16,260
Humiliating.

453
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:48,300
But getting into Yucai was your dream.

454
00:24:48,300 --> 00:24:49,780
It came true. You should be happy.

455
00:24:49,780 --> 00:24:50,980
The rest is grown-up stuff.

456
00:24:53,740 --> 00:24:55,101
I did want to go to Yucai.

457
00:24:55,901 --> 00:24:57,101
But I didn't want that chance

458
00:24:57,101 --> 00:24:59,060
to come from my mom marrying someone.

459
00:24:59,381 --> 00:25:00,341
Your mom can marry

460
00:25:00,341 --> 00:25:01,621
anyone but herself.

461
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:06,300
I don't want to owe him anything.

462
00:25:06,941 --> 00:25:08,421
Being beholden to him,

463
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:10,661
I can't be tough against him anymore.

464
00:25:11,341 --> 00:25:14,060
Well, why do you always
need to be so tough?

465
00:25:14,621 --> 00:25:15,740
Are you a rolling pin?

466
00:25:16,780 --> 00:25:18,460
Did your mom marry
for you to pick fights?

467
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:20,821
She might not care about dignity,
but I do.

468
00:25:21,540 --> 00:25:22,460
Who doesn't care?

469
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:24,181
You mean your mom?

470
00:25:27,141 --> 00:25:28,181
That's a low blow.

471
00:25:29,661 --> 00:25:31,540
It's hard for your mom
to raise you two alone.

472
00:25:31,821 --> 00:25:33,901
What's wrong with marrying someone
to share the load?

473
00:25:34,621 --> 00:25:36,220
Who doesn't want a better life?

474
00:25:37,101 --> 00:25:39,141
Marriage doesn't cost dignity.
Change your thinking.

475
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:41,220
Why are you taking her side?

476
00:25:42,141 --> 00:25:43,941
You've been too sheltered.

477
00:25:44,220 --> 00:25:45,821
Your mom supports the whole family.

478
00:25:46,581 --> 00:25:47,901
Have you ever earned a penny?

479
00:25:48,341 --> 00:25:50,220
Do you know how hard it is
to earn money?

480
00:25:52,381 --> 00:25:54,621
Come take a look. See what we've got!

481
00:25:54,740 --> 00:25:56,181
Hoodies, dresses, clearance sale!

482
00:25:56,300 --> 00:25:57,220
- Come see.
- How much?

483
00:25:57,300 --> 00:25:58,581
This one? Fifteen for this.

484
00:25:59,060 --> 00:25:59,980
Can I get it for ten?

485
00:26:00,181 --> 00:26:02,060
It's too low.
Fifteen is the lowest price.

486
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:03,661
See how stretchy this fabric is?

487
00:26:03,661 --> 00:26:04,260
No.

488
00:26:04,260 --> 00:26:05,181
It really suits you.

489
00:26:05,341 --> 00:26:06,581
- Miss.
- No.

490
00:26:10,460 --> 00:26:11,861
I'm moving to La City soon.

491
00:26:17,821 --> 00:26:18,861
It's many kilometers away.

492
00:26:22,821 --> 00:26:24,581
Come on, cheap stuff, super cheap.

493
00:26:24,581 --> 00:26:26,621
The cut is really good.

494
00:26:26,621 --> 00:26:28,020
Look over here. See what we've got.

495
00:26:28,621 --> 00:26:30,740
Here, how about this one? Like it?

496
00:26:32,341 --> 00:26:32,941
No.

497
00:26:37,941 --> 00:26:40,341
It'll be hard for us to meet
in the future.

498
00:26:50,581 --> 00:26:51,980
(Among all words,)

499
00:26:52,700 --> 00:26:54,220
('Hmm' is the weakest answer.)

500
00:26:55,381 --> 00:26:56,740
(It means not wanting this)

501
00:26:57,661 --> 00:26:58,740
(but being powerless.)

502
00:27:02,020 --> 00:27:04,821
Will you come see me off
on the day I leave?

503
00:27:06,941 --> 00:27:07,621
Are you done?

504
00:27:11,220 --> 00:27:12,020
Where are you going?

505
00:27:12,020 --> 00:27:12,661
I need to pee.

506
00:27:12,861 --> 00:27:13,901
Watch the stall for me.

507
00:27:20,780 --> 00:27:21,740
Well? Do you like it?

508
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:22,740
How much for it?

509
00:27:24,141 --> 00:27:25,381
- 50.
- How about 40?

510
00:27:25,941 --> 00:27:26,861
The fabric is nice.

511
00:27:26,861 --> 00:27:28,460
It's super comfy and cool in summer.

512
00:27:29,060 --> 00:27:29,780
Forty it is.

513
00:27:31,260 --> 00:27:32,260
Alright, I'll take one.

514
00:27:36,460 --> 00:27:36,980
Here you go.

515
00:27:38,861 --> 00:27:39,448
Here.

516
00:27:39,821 --> 00:27:40,341
Thanks.

517
00:27:40,901 --> 00:27:42,500
- See you.
- Come again!

518
00:27:46,740 --> 00:27:48,581
He Yuqiong, I made money for you.

519
00:27:48,980 --> 00:27:50,941
I sold that 15-yuan piece for 40.

520
00:27:53,661 --> 00:27:54,220
Thanks.

521
00:28:09,060 --> 00:28:11,581
Xiaofei, the car's here.

522
00:28:12,381 --> 00:28:13,980
Get your sister. We're leaving.
Hurry up.

523
00:28:21,260 --> 00:28:22,821
Turn off the lights and lock the door.

524
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:25,341
Keep it down. Don't wake the neighbors.

525
00:28:25,980 --> 00:28:26,540
Hurry up.

526
00:28:29,341 --> 00:28:29,901
Let's go.

527
00:28:32,060 --> 00:28:32,621
Let's go.

528
00:28:33,581 --> 00:28:34,552
Let's go.

529
00:28:40,341 --> 00:28:41,500
Xiaofei, help me.

530
00:28:42,020 --> 00:28:43,740
Alright. Good boy.

531
00:28:48,460 --> 00:28:49,260
Give it to me.

532
00:28:49,700 --> 00:28:50,980
Come on. Easy now.

533
00:28:56,101 --> 00:28:56,861
Xiaofei, get in.

534
00:28:59,141 --> 00:28:59,821
Xiaoming, hurry.

535
00:29:00,621 --> 00:29:01,141
Get in quick.

536
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:03,740
(It was my mom's third marriage.)

537
00:29:04,700 --> 00:29:06,500
(That morning,
we were sneaky like thieves.)

538
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:07,260
Get in the car.

539
00:29:08,581 --> 00:29:10,421
(I really didn't want
to get in that car.)

540
00:29:10,980 --> 00:29:11,700
Why stand there?

541
00:29:33,528 --> 00:29:36,964
(La City)

542
00:30:14,460 --> 00:30:16,381
You two need to properly thank Mr. Sun.

543
00:30:17,020 --> 00:30:19,101
Mr. Sun is our family's benefactor.

544
00:30:25,220 --> 00:30:26,300
Thank you, Mr. Sun.

545
00:30:27,141 --> 00:30:28,581
Benefactor sounds too formal.

546
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:30,661
Are we not a family united by fate?

547
00:30:32,381 --> 00:30:33,141
Right, Xiaoming?

548
00:30:45,336 --> 00:30:47,941
Yeah, quite fated.

549
00:31:08,060 --> 00:31:10,581
Come on, everyone inside.

550
00:31:12,060 --> 00:31:12,700
Come in.

551
00:31:16,901 --> 00:31:18,381
From now on, this is your own home.

552
00:31:18,381 --> 00:31:19,341
Get comfortable.

553
00:31:21,581 --> 00:31:22,540
Where should I put this?

554
00:31:23,101 --> 00:31:23,740
Put it here.

555
00:31:25,661 --> 00:31:26,581
Big couch!

556
00:31:27,821 --> 00:31:30,540
Know why I told you not to bring
all that junk from the old place?

557
00:31:30,581 --> 00:31:32,500
- I have everything here.
- So comfy!

558
00:31:34,101 --> 00:31:35,661
Change into your slippers.

559
00:31:36,101 --> 00:31:38,220
If you dirty the floor,
your mom will be mopping it.

560
00:31:38,220 --> 00:31:38,901
Hurry up.

561
00:31:40,780 --> 00:31:41,341
Come on.

562
00:31:48,141 --> 00:31:50,020
- I told you not to bring anything.
- Yours.

563
00:31:50,020 --> 00:31:52,220
- You brought a lot.
- Yours. And mine.

564
00:31:54,500 --> 00:31:55,576
No room for them.

565
00:31:56,740 --> 00:31:58,392
Come on, let me show you around.

566
00:32:00,300 --> 00:32:01,861
For sweeping, we have a vacuum cleaner.

567
00:32:03,020 --> 00:32:05,020
For laundry,
a fully automatic washing machine.

568
00:32:05,381 --> 00:32:06,540
We have everything, see?

569
00:32:06,821 --> 00:32:08,060
It's a big three-bedroom.

570
00:32:08,381 --> 00:32:09,780
Everyone gets their own room.

571
00:32:10,260 --> 00:32:11,480
- Okay?
- A big three-bedroom.

572
00:32:11,621 --> 00:32:13,060
You two will have your own rooms.

573
00:32:13,060 --> 00:32:13,901
Now come look here.

574
00:32:14,901 --> 00:32:15,901
These big windows.

575
00:32:17,621 --> 00:32:18,460
The light comes in.

576
00:32:18,740 --> 00:32:20,780
If you say something is missing,
there's one thing.

577
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:22,060
You.

578
00:32:25,341 --> 00:32:25,941
Sun.

579
00:32:26,661 --> 00:32:28,181
Turn on the imported speakers

580
00:32:28,181 --> 00:32:29,341
to blow the kids away.

581
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:30,460
Sure thing.

582
00:32:30,581 --> 00:32:32,181
Let me check out my domain.

583
00:32:32,901 --> 00:32:33,421
Here.

584
00:32:37,460 --> 00:32:39,901
Oven, microwave.

585
00:32:40,821 --> 00:32:43,220
Sun, you even bought a dishwasher?

586
00:32:44,941 --> 00:32:46,500
A machine for washing dishes?

587
00:32:47,101 --> 00:32:48,300
- Of course we need one.
- Xiaoming,

588
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:50,341
- It wastes water and electricity.
- we won't need karaoke bars.

589
00:32:50,341 --> 00:32:52,381
- We can sing at home.
(- Meiyan, your delicate hands.)

590
00:32:52,381 --> 00:32:54,540
- Is this your home? Saying it so easily.
(- Washing dishes by hand)

591
00:32:54,540 --> 00:32:55,661
(will get your hands rough.)

592
00:32:55,941 --> 00:32:58,101
Not soft anymore, right?

593
00:32:58,861 --> 00:32:59,500
And your face.

594
00:33:06,381 --> 00:33:07,581
Tonight, I'm making dumplings.

595
00:33:07,581 --> 00:33:08,901
Make room in your stomachs.

596
00:33:14,341 --> 00:33:16,220
Xiaoming, this is your room.

597
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:19,661
How nice.

598
00:33:20,700 --> 00:33:22,060
I even want to live here.

599
00:33:33,460 --> 00:33:33,980
Xiaoming.

600
00:33:35,941 --> 00:33:37,381
It's okay. You can read these books.

601
00:33:37,861 --> 00:33:39,980
After reading them,
return them to their places.

602
00:33:40,220 --> 00:33:41,661
These books all belong to Yuanyuan.

603
00:33:44,941 --> 00:33:47,220
Also, you can stay
in this room normally.

604
00:33:47,341 --> 00:33:48,460
But about your stuff,

605
00:33:48,941 --> 00:33:49,540
just...

606
00:33:50,220 --> 00:33:51,780
Just put it in Xiaofei's room.

607
00:33:52,941 --> 00:33:55,661
Yuanyuan will come back
now and then for the weekend.

608
00:33:55,661 --> 00:33:57,581
If she sees her room occupied,

609
00:33:57,581 --> 00:33:59,621
she'll definitely be upset, right?

610
00:34:03,700 --> 00:34:04,861
Wait, Xiaoming.

611
00:34:05,101 --> 00:34:06,260
Xiaofei, your room is here.

612
00:34:06,621 --> 00:34:07,581
This room, come on.

613
00:34:08,381 --> 00:34:09,112
Come on.

614
00:34:10,500 --> 00:34:12,221
Well? You'll have it to yourself.
Big, huh?

615
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:14,821
Isn't this just a storage room?

616
00:34:16,660 --> 00:34:19,020
When you have time,
help him clean up all this stuff

617
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:20,580
and tidy it up. Put everything here.

618
00:34:21,180 --> 00:34:22,341
How nice, right?

619
00:34:22,460 --> 00:34:24,221
See, there's plenty of sunlight.

620
00:34:25,341 --> 00:34:26,136
Right?

621
00:34:27,620 --> 00:34:30,941
Come on, let the four of us celebrate.

622
00:34:38,580 --> 00:34:39,832
I'll take the living room.

623
00:34:40,140 --> 00:34:41,656
My stuff will be in Xiaofei's room.

624
00:34:42,781 --> 00:34:44,540
There's plenty of space. Stop acting up.

625
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:45,460
Aren't there two rooms?

626
00:34:45,460 --> 00:34:46,821
One room each is perfect.

627
00:34:48,140 --> 00:34:49,781
I'm moving into the dorm next Monday.

628
00:34:49,781 --> 00:34:51,261
I can return only two days a week.

629
00:34:51,660 --> 00:34:52,821
No need to take up that room.

630
00:34:55,020 --> 00:34:55,901
Let me help you.

631
00:35:03,701 --> 00:35:05,221
Xiaoming, there's...

632
00:35:05,821 --> 00:35:06,460
Don't mind her.

633
00:35:07,460 --> 00:35:08,741
She just doesn't play along.

634
00:35:10,301 --> 00:35:11,941
Come on, cheers.

635
00:35:12,261 --> 00:35:12,781
Cheers.

636
00:35:37,421 --> 00:35:38,460
(I slept on that couch)

637
00:35:38,460 --> 00:35:39,660
(for over two years.)

638
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:43,180
(But that place
was never really my home.)

639
00:35:54,861 --> 00:35:58,020
(Not long after arriving in La City,
Bai Shu and I made up.)

640
00:35:59,701 --> 00:36:01,261
(We forgot who made the first move.)

641
00:36:02,301 --> 00:36:04,180
(Anyway, we made up.)

642
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:06,821
(And we were even closer.)

643
00:36:11,180 --> 00:36:12,741
(It feels so good to have friends.)

644
00:36:16,540 --> 00:36:17,140
Xiaoming.

645
00:36:19,261 --> 00:36:20,660
What are you two doing here?

646
00:36:21,060 --> 00:36:22,301
We came to see you guys.

647
00:36:22,781 --> 00:36:23,861
Come on, let's go out.

648
00:36:25,341 --> 00:36:26,060
Where to?

649
00:36:26,301 --> 00:36:27,301
I know a great spot.

650
00:36:27,301 --> 00:36:28,660
But we must return to Qidaohezi.

651
00:36:29,341 --> 00:36:30,500
That far?

652
00:36:31,180 --> 00:36:32,120
We have this afternoon.

653
00:36:32,221 --> 00:36:33,460
We can go grab a good meal.

654
00:36:34,421 --> 00:36:36,020
Guo Bao Rou at Friendship Eatery?

655
00:36:36,140 --> 00:36:36,781
Okay.

656
00:36:36,821 --> 00:36:37,620
I miss it so much.

657
00:36:37,620 --> 00:36:38,261
Then let's go.

658
00:36:38,861 --> 00:36:40,301
- Palm or Back.
- Palm or Back.

659
00:36:41,821 --> 00:36:43,060
- Palm or Back.
- Palm or Back.

660
00:36:43,620 --> 00:36:45,112
- Palm or Back.
- Palm or Back.

661
00:36:45,701 --> 00:36:46,660
I win.

662
00:36:46,980 --> 00:36:49,180
The last piece of Guo Bao Rou is mine.

663
00:36:53,821 --> 00:36:54,980
Sir, we're finished.

664
00:36:55,460 --> 00:36:56,408
You're done?

665
00:36:59,460 --> 00:37:00,381
Let's play a game.

666
00:37:01,020 --> 00:37:01,540
What game?

667
00:37:02,180 --> 00:37:03,580
Truth or Dare.

668
00:37:03,821 --> 00:37:04,580
We spin the bottle.

669
00:37:04,580 --> 00:37:05,381
Bottle points,

670
00:37:05,381 --> 00:37:07,460
and the one
gets to choose truth or dare.

671
00:37:07,544 --> 00:37:08,440
Okay.

672
00:37:11,901 --> 00:37:12,600
Let's go.

673
00:37:13,781 --> 00:37:15,460
- Truth.
- Truth.

674
00:37:15,500 --> 00:37:17,020
- Truth.
- Truth it is.

675
00:37:17,540 --> 00:37:19,901
Tell me, did you scatter those nails
that punctured my tire?

676
00:37:20,901 --> 00:37:21,592
No.

677
00:37:23,341 --> 00:37:25,741
- Truth, truth, truth.
- Truth.

678
00:37:26,020 --> 00:37:27,140
He scattered them.

679
00:37:27,901 --> 00:37:28,460
No.

680
00:37:28,821 --> 00:37:31,100
Yes, she said to scatter them.

681
00:37:31,100 --> 00:37:31,701
I just did it.

682
00:37:31,701 --> 00:37:32,901
Which hand scattered them?

683
00:37:34,701 --> 00:37:35,781
Truth.

684
00:37:36,020 --> 00:37:36,781
Truth.

685
00:37:36,901 --> 00:37:37,741
This hand did.

686
00:37:42,020 --> 00:37:45,060
Alright, considering how well
we've gotten along this year,

687
00:37:45,460 --> 00:37:46,381
I'll forgive you two.

688
00:37:49,540 --> 00:37:50,296
Again.

689
00:37:55,341 --> 00:37:57,140
What are you doing? You...

690
00:37:57,261 --> 00:38:00,381
- Truth.
- Truth.

691
00:38:00,381 --> 00:38:01,221
- No, I won't.
- Truth.

692
00:38:01,221 --> 00:38:02,500
Quit stalling. I'll take a dare.

693
00:38:02,821 --> 00:38:04,660
Go outside and shout the name
of the girl

694
00:38:04,660 --> 00:38:05,752
you like three times.

695
00:38:10,100 --> 00:38:10,712
- No.
- Fine.

696
00:38:10,821 --> 00:38:11,660
Isn't it weird

697
00:38:11,660 --> 00:38:13,528
- to let him shout on the road?
- It's fine.

698
00:38:22,901 --> 00:38:24,381
I like...

699
00:38:32,100 --> 00:38:33,620
Maggie Cheung!

700
00:38:33,980 --> 00:38:35,620
I like Maggie Cheung!

701
00:38:35,781 --> 00:38:37,620
I love you, Maggie Cheung!

702
00:38:37,741 --> 00:38:39,660
(Friendship Eatery)
I love you, Maggie Cheung!

703
00:38:42,861 --> 00:38:44,741
That doesn't count. No celebrity's name.

704
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:45,821
Give us someone we know.

705
00:38:45,821 --> 00:38:46,341
Impressive.

706
00:38:48,261 --> 00:38:48,901
Enough.

707
00:38:49,701 --> 00:38:51,460
Shouting who he likes from the curb

708
00:38:51,620 --> 00:38:52,600
is embarrassing enough.

709
00:38:52,861 --> 00:38:53,861
I couldn't do it at all.

710
00:38:57,741 --> 00:38:58,781
Shameless.

711
00:39:01,221 --> 00:39:02,381
Okay, let's hurry and go

712
00:39:02,620 --> 00:39:03,580
to the spot I mentioned

713
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:05,020
before it gets dark.

714
00:39:05,020 --> 00:39:05,941
- Let's go.
- Okay.

715
00:39:06,020 --> 00:39:06,980
- Let's go.
- Okay.

716
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:16,381
(Friendship Eatery)

717
00:39:16,381 --> 00:39:17,460
What are you doing?

718
00:39:17,701 --> 00:39:18,261
Coming.

719
00:39:18,261 --> 00:39:18,861
Hurry up!

720
00:39:24,285 --> 00:39:26,621
(Friendship Forever)

721
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,653
(Forever)

722
00:39:37,261 --> 00:39:38,980
Qidaohezi has a place like this?

723
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:40,941
It has tons of abandoned factories.

724
00:39:41,500 --> 00:39:42,620
Like this glass factory

725
00:39:42,861 --> 00:39:44,261
and the optical factories there.

726
00:39:46,020 --> 00:39:46,980
Isn't that...

727
00:39:47,140 --> 00:39:49,060
Yeah, my parents
used to work right here.

728
00:39:49,301 --> 00:39:50,580
I used to play around here.

729
00:39:51,701 --> 00:39:53,100
Back then, the factory's faucets

730
00:39:53,100 --> 00:39:54,381
dispensed chilled orange juice.

731
00:39:54,861 --> 00:39:55,861
You know what? Back then,

732
00:39:56,100 --> 00:39:57,460
we'd fill huge mugs like this.

733
00:39:57,781 --> 00:39:58,500
How big a mug?

734
00:39:58,980 --> 00:39:59,741
This big giant mug.

735
00:39:59,741 --> 00:40:02,821
Goodness, that must have been
so satisfying to drink.

736
00:40:02,980 --> 00:40:03,861
- Super.
- My stomach

737
00:40:03,861 --> 00:40:04,821
was full of soda.

738
00:40:04,821 --> 00:40:05,500
Get out of here.

739
00:40:06,180 --> 00:40:07,140
Stop talking nonsense.

740
00:40:07,540 --> 00:40:08,701
Don't always hit people.

741
00:40:08,901 --> 00:40:10,301
Anyway, when I told people later,

742
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:12,100
they said I was making it up.

743
00:40:17,060 --> 00:40:18,221
Why are they running so fast?

744
00:40:20,261 --> 00:40:20,920
Come on.

745
00:40:25,100 --> 00:40:25,816
This way.

746
00:40:31,580 --> 00:40:32,381
How about over here?

747
00:40:35,301 --> 00:40:36,301
Isn't this hall huge?

748
00:40:36,980 --> 00:40:39,020
I watched my first movie here
when I was a kid.

749
00:40:39,460 --> 00:40:40,500
I loved the front row.

750
00:40:40,500 --> 00:40:41,341
It felt amazing.

751
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:44,221
Watching movies on this big screen
must be awesome.

752
00:40:44,821 --> 00:40:45,540
Absolutely.

753
00:40:46,808 --> 00:40:48,500
I'll see if the projector's still there.

754
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:49,221
I'll go too.

755
00:40:49,781 --> 00:40:50,580
You two wait here.

756
00:40:58,020 --> 00:40:59,100
We fixed it.

757
00:40:59,100 --> 00:41:00,821
See if there's any film.
Let's show a movie.

758
00:41:01,180 --> 00:41:02,140
Alright, let's go.

759
00:41:02,421 --> 00:41:03,140
Look.

760
00:41:15,540 --> 00:41:16,381
What? What?

761
00:41:24,781 --> 00:41:25,620
Fire!

762
00:41:25,620 --> 00:41:26,140
Fire!

763
00:41:26,140 --> 00:41:26,741
Let's go!

764
00:41:26,741 --> 00:41:27,620
Fire! Get out!

765
00:41:34,741 --> 00:41:36,301
Are you two sure you don't need help?

766
00:41:36,301 --> 00:41:38,104
There's so much smoke. Gosh.

767
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:46,341
What are you two doing?

768
00:41:46,781 --> 00:41:48,301
Disgusting men are so annoying!

769
00:41:50,781 --> 00:41:51,381
Seriously.

770
00:41:53,701 --> 00:41:54,381
I'm choking.

771
00:42:03,180 --> 00:42:05,180
He Yuqiong, you are so disgusting.

772
00:42:05,381 --> 00:42:06,821
How could you pee on the projector?

773
00:42:09,701 --> 00:42:12,781
If it weren't for that pee,
the auditorium would be gone, alright?

774
00:42:13,221 --> 00:42:13,980
Where's Bai Shu?

775
00:42:14,301 --> 00:42:14,941
Where's Bai Shu?

776
00:42:18,301 --> 00:42:19,100
I know where she is.

777
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:20,100
Follow me.

778
00:42:22,861 --> 00:42:23,421
Bai Shu?

779
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:25,100
Bai Shu?

780
00:42:26,540 --> 00:42:27,480
What's she looking at?

781
00:42:29,901 --> 00:42:30,980
How did you come here?

782
00:42:33,460 --> 00:42:34,140
Look.

783
00:42:36,301 --> 00:42:37,620
That's where we were born.

784
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:41,221
But from here,

785
00:42:43,261 --> 00:42:44,421
it looks so unfamiliar.

786
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
